{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Bring the date for the post-study work visa closer to help current students",
        "additional_details": "It is a big achievement to be reintroducing the 2-year post-study work visa after it was removed by Theresa May in 2012 \u2014 I am so glad to see such a progressive step towards building a stronger global community here in the UK. \r\n\r\nStories of a few current international students that could benefit from this are available here: https://bbc.in/2Q4WXKi\r\n\r\nFurther details on the new visa can be found here: http://bit.ly/2PZFCSL",
        "background": "I would like to request the government to bring the date for the 2-year post-study work visa closer to help current international students (i.e. students graduating before 2021) benefit from this too. It would be unfair to current international students otherwise.",
